BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EHsJc13jRJqposppf--Xi
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260315T233350Z
DTSTART:20260326T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Pioneer Park\n\nJoin us for an afternoon work party in Pionee r
	 Park. This beautiful habitat is being threatened by non-native weeds\, su
	ch as ivy and blackberry. Ivy plays a big role in local habitat destructi 
	on by pulling down trees\, shading out native plants\, and reducing biodiv
	ersity. Join in our efforts and help to create a healthier forest. \n\nA l
	l ages welcome\, and no experience necessary! Gloves\, tools\, water\, an 
	d small snacks provided.\n\nWhen: Thursday\, March 26th\, 4pm-6pm\n\nWhere
	: Pioneer Park SE\, Meet at the corner of Island Crest Way and SE 68th St.
	 Follow VOLUNTEER EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in c
	loth es you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: long pants\, boots or sneak
	ers\\). Bring water. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided.\n
	\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup.org/CWRCR\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amc
	ity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer-park/18066420/2026-03-2
	6T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer
	-park/18066420/2026-03-26T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
